editorialSummary.text: Upscale resource for furniture, decorative accessories, lighting, tableware & textiles, plus a cafe.

originalText.text: Absolutely beautiful! Like walking into a museum! The items all hand crafted by the most skilled artist and designers. Chantel, (I'm sorry if I forgot your name) and Kevin are 2 of my new favorite people EVER! Incredible vibe, textures, plants, lighting. I didn't exactly  know what to expect when I first went in but it was well above and beyond what i sort of was thinking. The restaurant is a whole other story. I envy those that can afford to shop here! It may be expensive but the quality, the story, is worth it.

originalText.text:
The best way to describe this store is as follows. Your aunt from Cote de Provence met your friend from Bali, and they made a life in Madagascar.

Each piece is very unique and tells its own story. A story of elegance, culture, and a healthy portfolio.

Perfect place to purchase a signature piece or pieces that bring you joy to splurge on.

originalText.text:
Title: A Design Lover's Paradise: Roman & Williams Guild

Rating: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Review:

Nestled in the heart of New York City, Roman & Williams Guild on 53 Howard Street is a design lover's paradise that will leave you in awe of its impeccable craftsmanship, curated collections, and exquisite attention to detail. From the moment you step foot into this extraordinary space, you'll be transported to a world where art, design, and creativity converge.

Roman & Williams Guild is more than just a store; it's a haven for those who appreciate the beauty and artistry of finely crafted furniture, home decor, and lifestyle products. The space itself is a masterpiece, with its high ceilings, natural light, and carefully curated displays that showcase the best of contemporary design.

The collections at Roman & Williams Guild are a testament to the founders' impeccable taste and their commitment to showcasing the work of talented artisans and designers. From handcrafted furniture to unique lighting fixtures and one-of-a-kind home accessories, every piece in the store tells a story and exudes a sense of timeless elegance.

One of the highlights of our visit to Roman & Williams Guild was the knowledgeable and friendly staff. They are passionate about design and are always ready to offer insights, recommendations, and guidance to help you find the perfect piece for your home or a thoughtful gift for a loved one. Their expertise and genuine enthusiasm for design make the shopping experience truly enjoyable and inspiring.

The attention to detail at Roman & Williams Guild is second to none. From the carefully curated displays to the thoughtfully designed packaging, every aspect of the shopping experience is a testament to the founders' commitment to quality and craftsmanship. The store's aesthetic is a perfect blend of modern and vintage, creating a unique atmosphere that is both inviting and inspiring.

Whether you're a design aficionado or simply appreciate the beauty of well-crafted objects, Roman & Williams Guild is a must-visit destination in New York City. The store is a treasure trove of inspiration, where you can explore a carefully curated selection of products and immerse yourself in the world of design.

In conclusion, Roman & Williams Guild is a design lover's dream come true. The store's impeccable taste, curated collections, and commitment to quality make it a standout destination in New York City. Whether you're looking to furnish your home with timeless pieces or simply seeking inspiration, Roman & Williams Guild will exceed your expectations and leave you with a newfound appreciation for the artistry of design.

So, if you find yourself in New York City, make sure to pay a visit to Roman & Williams Guild on 53 Howard Street. Prepare to be inspired, captivated, and enchanted by the world of design that awaits you.
